## Agent skills policy

Cursor Collections ships many optional `eversis-*` skills. **Presence in `.cursor/skills/` does not mean every skill applies to this repo.** Before `eversis_skills_get`, read this section and any `docs/context/*.md` filter/stack notes.

### Always applicable (this framework repo)

| Skill | When |
| ----- | ---- |
| `eversis-fine-handoff` | Fine turn after `@eversis-implement` |
| `eversis-creating-skills`, `eversis-creating-prompts`, `eversis-creating-agents`, `eversis-creating-instructions` | Framework customization work |

### Load when task and stack match

| Skill | Load when |
| ----- | --------- |
| `eversis-writing-repo-documentation` | README, CHANGELOG, `website/docs` updates |
| `eversis-orchestrating-implementation` | `@eversis-implement` orchestration (via MCP or prompt) |

### Do not load in this repo (unless plan explicitly requires)

| Skill | Reason |
| ----- | ------ |
| `eversis-implementing-filters` | No product list UIs — framework/docs repo only |
| `eversis-implementing-backend`, `eversis-implementing-frontend` | No application backend/frontend in scope |
| `eversis-ba-docs-planner`, `eversis-ba-docs-writer` | Word `.docx` release docs — not this repo's workflow |

**Consumer projects:** replace this section with your product stack (Next, Nest, Liferay, etc.). See `documentation/cursor-collection.md` § Agent skills policy.

